          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0622P0-05898'>
        <a name='S5LV0622P0_20010301_GCR_321'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-malcolm-sinclair' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0622P0_20010301_GCR_321' title='Link to this speech by Mr Malcolm Sinclair' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-malcolm-sinclair" title="Mr Malcolm Sinclair">The Earl of Caithness</a></cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            Another rain forest is cut down at the same time.</p><p>
            On a serious point, I was confused by the point made by the noble Lord, Lord McIntosh of Haringey, on common parts. He said that the management could be done either by the landlord or by the management company&#x2014;at least, that is what I thought he said.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0622P0-05899'>
        <a name='S5LV0622P0_20010301_GCR_322'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-andrew-mcintosh' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0622P0_20010301_GCR_322' title='Link to this speech by Mr Andrew McIntosh' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-andrew-mcintosh" title="Mr Andrew McIntosh">Lord McIntosh of Haringey</a></cite>
